            "text_XmrwTY": {
              "type": "text",
              "settings": {
                "text": "<p>Scent can evoke relaxation or exhilaration, comfort or courage. It can stimulate and it can soothe, because the sense of smell is a direct channel to the limbic system, the area of the brain where emotions and memories are processed. The study of this connection between aromas and human psychology is known as aromachology.</p><p></p><p>By combining traditional artisan perfumery techniques with the latest research in aromachology, our scent scientists, led by our founder Victor Alarcon, a scent scientist himself, use fragrances to stimulate chemical reactions in the brain. These reactions trigger feelings, unlock memories, and create moods.</p><p>Our natural fragrances can also help restore biochemical, hormonal, and emotional balance, allowing us to tune into our consciousness and elevate our spirit.</p>",
                "width": "fit-content",
                "max_width": "narrow",
                "alignment": "left",
